node.text:
I’ve often been asked the question, “how do you feel about faux plants?”. The answer is simple, not everyone has the light or the care level to have living plants in their space. So I’d rather you bring in a faux plant than force a living plant into a space where it will suffer and eventually die.  Faux plants can elevate spots in your home where you never thought you’d be able to have greenery before. With all of the faux plants in the Hilton Carter for Target collection, my goal was to make them look as real as possible so that they could really bring that lush, calm feeling. Here are a few tips on where and how to style them! 🌿🙏🏾💚

node.text: Over the holidays I partnered with @stgermaindrinks to develop some WILD ideas for entertaining during holiday season. To pull off these themed moments, I teamed up with the talented @sashabikoff and @madamebleu_stgermain. Inspired by the interactive nature of the Parisian salons in the 1920s, we chose three art movements from that time (Art Deco, Cubism and Surrealism) to take our holiday gatherings to the next level. Here are the highlights from the Surrealist nightcap moment and how it all came together! If you missed the Art Deco or Cubism moments, you can find them here in my IGTV. Enjoy! #StGermainPartner #SalonStGermain

node.text: Over the holidays I partnered with @stgermaindrinks to develop some WILD ideas for entertaining during holiday season. To pull off these themed moments, I teamed up with the talented @sashabikoff and @madamebleu_stgermain. Inspired by the interactive nature of the Parisian salons in the 1920s, we chose three art movements from that time (Art Deco, Cubism and Surrealism) to take our holiday gatherings to the next level. Here are the highlights from the Art Deco entry moment and how it all came together! I will be sharing the Cubism and Surrealism moments over the next week. Enjoy! #StGermainPartner #SalonStGermain

I just partnered with @ppgpaints to freshen up the living room of a friend’s home and to simultaneously show off the beauty and durability of their Timeless paint #PPGPartner. Here you can see the process from start to finish. My intentions were to use a palette of vibrant colors to create a hand painted mural! The trick is selecting the right colors. For this project I chose a color palette that would lend itself to the greenery that was in the home but would also allow the plants to pop against the wall. My inspiration was “plants in terra cotta pots”. I used colors like their NIGHT WATCH(the darker green), LIGHT SAGE and LIME SPRITZ to anchor the project in greens and the color GEORGIAN LEATHER(the orange) to play off of the terra cotta planters, wood flooring and leather furniture. What I love about @ppgpaints is how easy the application was. It made the process less stressful and when looking to have a little fun painting a design on your wall, that is everything. With the new stain resistant formula, it helps you to keep your project looking vibrant and new by just wiping away any dirt or dust with ease. This was perfect for the fireplace, mantle and doorway, which can get dusty and marked up easily. No one likes to style the top of a mantle more than I do and over time the paint there can take a bit of abuse. Having the ability to just wipe away any stains here is a plus. I hope you enjoy watching my painting process as it all came together. Visit http://bit.ly/Hilton-Carter to see how your own project could come to life! #PPGTimeless
